HEADWORD: Enchodus
<hw>En"cho*dus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ a spear + <grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, a tooth.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of extinct Cretaceous fishes; -- so
named from their spear-shaped teeth. They were allied to the pike
(<gen>Esox</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enchondroma</ent>⟦br⟧
